WARRI  – Poor funding of Research and Development has been identified as a key factor hindering technological advancement in Nigeria. Dr. Henry Adimula, Principal /Chief Executive Officer of Petroleum Training lnstitute( PTI) Effurun Delta State, made this observation when he spoke with Daily lndependent Newspaper Correspondent in his office recently. He noted that those nations that are making a lot of Waves in technological breakthroughs spend so much to achieve that purpose. He lamented that our policy makers need to do certain things differently to enable the nation advance forward faster in the pursuit of the technology that will make the necessary impact in our today living. Speaking further, he identified consistency and focus as another important ingredient that we need to consider in making Nigeria a realistic player.